text: Natalya Kurnosova (born 11 September 1975) is a Russian volleyball player. She played at the 2005 Women's European Volleyball Championship, winning a bronze medal. and 2006 FIVB Women's World Championship. She played for WVC Dynamo Moscow, CSKA Moscow, and Proton-Saratov. She was part of the 2005/2006 Russian Women's Volleyball Championship team. == References == == Other websites == * Dynamo Moscow volleyball players Natalia Hanikoglu and Natalia Kurnosova alamy Category:1975 births Category:Russian volleyball players Category:Living people
